hopobject.body: We were at school together clicks pharmacy assistance learnership programme The legislation I've introduced with Senators Tom Coburn,R-Okla., Richard Burr,R-N.C., and Johnny Isakson,R-Ga., would set rates at the May auction rate of the 10-year treasury bond, plus 3 percent. This would mean that 100 percent of all new student loans made this year would have a rate below 5 percent. Almost all Senate Republicans voted to support this solution on June 6.
